INSERT INTO `books` VALUES (1914,1,'top','The Shining City','1_1','','9780451460806','Charged with murder and treason, half-human Rhiannon, awaiting trial in Sorrowgate Tower, is plagued by prophetic dreams involving the spiteful ghost of an evil queen and discovers that a princess, using forbidden magic, has cast a spell on her lover, Lewen. Original.','April 4, 2006','B&N'),(1915,1,'top','The Witches of Eileanan','1_1','','9780451456892','The first book in a trilogy of Celtic fantasy is set in the magical land of Eileanan, where the young Isabeau, brought up by an elderly witch, leads a horde of persecuted witches eager to topple the evil queen. Original.','July 1, 1998','B&N'),(1916,1,'top','The cursed towers','1_1','n/a','9780451456915','','1999','B&N'),(1917,1,'top','The Fathomless Caves','1_1','','9780451459022','In the epic conclusion of The Witches of Eileanan series, Iseult, her sister, Isabeau, and Iseult\'s beloved Lachlan risk everything to bring final peace, as the sea-dwelling Fairgean, driven by ancient hatreds, vow to destroy all those who dwell on the land. Original.','November 1, 2002','B&N'),(1918,1,'top','Infinite Crisis: The Novel','125_1','','9780441018956','','June 29, 2010','B&N'),(1919,1,'top','The Tower Of Ravens','1_1','','9780451460325','Condemned by her people for lacking the horns prized by her people, Rhiannon\'s only chance for escape is to capture one of the land\'s legendary flying horses and ride it to freedom, as she finds refuge in the home of Lewen, a young apprentice witch, and joins forces with him to save all Eileanan from the dark forces that threaten the land. Original.','June 7, 2005','B&N'),(1920,1,'top','The skull of the world','1_1','n/a','9780451458698','','','B&N'),(1921,1,'top','The Last Days of Krypton','3_1','','9780062219855','','December 4, 2012','B&N'),(1922,1,'top','Enemies & Allies','3_1','','9780062213808','','December 4, 2012','B&N'),(1923,1,'top','Confessor','4_1','n/a','9780765315236','','','B&N'),(1924,1,'top','The Pillars of creation','4_1','n/a','9780765300263','','','B&N'),(1925,1,'top','Lord of the Isles','5_1','','9780812522402','Mysteriously transported one thousand years into the future after a cataclysm destroys the empire of the Isles, a woman sorcerer finds herself in a small town, far from the centers of power, where she and a small group of individuals become the focus of aMysteriously transported one thousand years into the future after a cataclysm destroys the empire of the Isles, a woman sorcerer finds herself in a small town, far from the centers of power, where she and a small group of individuals become the focus of a new struggle for dominance. Reissue. new struggle for dominance. Reprint.','August 1, 1998','B&N'),(1926,1,'top','King\'s Dragon','6_1','','9780886777715','Set in an alternate Europe where bloody conflicts rage and sorcery holds sway, a young man seeking the destiny promised him by the Lady of Battles and a young woman gifted with a power that can alter the course of history are swept into a conflict for the survival of humanity. Reprint.','February 1, 1998','B&N'),(1927,1,'top','Prince of Dogs','6_1','','9780886778163','In the sequel to King\'s Dragon, a finalist for the Nebula Award for Best Novel, the Prince of Dogs, King Henry\'s illegitimate and immortal son, is held captive by an Eika warlord, while Liath searches for the secret of her past. Original.','February 1, 1999','B&N'),(1928,1,'top','The Burning Stone','6_1','','9780886778156','In the epic sequel to King\'s Dragon and Prince of Dogs, outcast lovers Liath and Sanglant flee King Henry\'s camp, only to discover that they must choose between the powerful demands of politics, forbidden knowledge, and family, as the time approaches when the lands of Aoi and human will once again be united. Reprint.','August 1, 2000','B&N'),(1929,1,'top','Child of Flame','6_1','','9780756400149','In the sequel to The Burning Stone, Alain becomes caught in the middle of an ancient conflict between humankind and the Cursed Ones, while Liath is kidnapped by strange alien creatires and forced into a difficult trial in a land of exile, and Sanglant, mourning the loss of his wife, Liath, struggles to warn King Henry of a deadly conspiracy of sorcerers. Reprint.','November 1, 2001','B&N'),(1930,1,'top','The Gathering Storm','6_1','','9780756401320','Liath, burdened with the knowledge that a cataclysmic event is approaching, finds her way back to Sanglant after four years, while Alain\'s life is in the hands of the Eika leader Stronghand, who saves him from a terrible fate. Reprint.','February 1, 2004','B&N'),(1931,1,'top','The Belgariad: Pawn of Prophecy, Queen of Sorcery, Magician\'s Gambit','7_1','','9780345456328','','August 1, 2002','B&N'),(1932,1,'top','The Belgariad: Castle of Wizardry/Enchanters\' End Game','7_1',NULL,'9780345456311','An omnibus edition featuring the final two novels in the epic saga includes Castle of Wizardry in which Garion regains the Orb and struggles to escape from the brutal Murgo soldiers and the deadly magic spells of Grolim Hierachs, and Enchanters\' End Game in which Garion is crowned as Overlord of the West, while in the East, the evil God Torak is about to awaken and challenge Garion\'s rule. Original.','September 1, 2002','B&N'),(1933,1,'top','Witch wraith','8_1','n/a','9780345523532','','','B&N'),(1934,1,'top','Decisive : how to make better choices in life and work','9_1','n/a','9780307956392','','2013','B&N'),(1935,1,'top','Beyond Belief: Awaken Potential, Focus Leadership','125_1','','9780578131009','The word leadership has been grossly overused to the point that many do not know what it really means and are unaware of the personal commitment required. Today\'s interconnected world, with its serious economic, environmental, and social challenges, cries out urgently for real leadership, yet few know what it is or how to develop it. Beyond Belief: Awaken Potential, Focus Leadership uses seven powerful models, case studies,